<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Angelo — Nutrition & Recomp</title>
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=IBM+Plex+Mono:wght@400;500;600&family=IBM+Plex+Sans:wght@400;500;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/Chart.js/4.4.1/chart.umd.js"></script>
<style>
  :root{
    --bg:#f6f8fa; --surface:#ffffff; --raised:#eef3f7; --border:#dde5ec;
    --border-s:#c4d2dd;
    --text:#1b2733; --head:#15222e; --t2:#5a6b7a; --t3:#90a0ad;
    --coral:#0e9aa7; --orange:#df8a3c; --gold:#caa53a; --pink:#c2607f; --violet:#7b6cb0; --sky:#3a8fb5;
    --green:#2e9e6b; --red:#d6604a;
    --d:'IBM Plex Sans',sans-serif; --b:'IBM Plex Sans',sans-serif; --m:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;
    --sunset:linear-gradient(90deg,#0e9aa7,#36b6bf);
  }
  *{box-sizing:border-box;margin:0;padding:0}
  body{background:var(--bg);color:var(--text);font-family:var(--b);line-height:1.5;padding:0 0 3rem}
  .wrap{max-width:1000px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 18px}
  .sr-only{position:absolute;width:1px;height:1px;overflow:hidden;clip:rect(0 0 0 0)}
  header{position:relative;padding:30px 0 20px;margin-bottom:22px;overflow:hidden}
  header::before{content:'';position:absolute;inset:0;background:
     radial-gradient(120% 90% at 92% -30%,rgba(14,154,167,0.10),transparent 60%);
     pointer-events:none}
  .hbar{height:4px;width:64px;background:var(--sunset);border-radius:3px;margin-bottom:16px}
  .eyebrow{font-family:var(--m);font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.14em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--coral);margin-bottom:8px}
  h1{font-family:var(--d);font-weight:600;font-size:32px;letter-spacing:-0.02em;line-height:1.05;color:var(--head)}
  .sub{color:var(--t2);font-size:13.5px;margin-top:7px}
  nav{display:flex;gap:4px;margin:22px 0 20px;flex-wrap:wrap}
  .tab{font-family:var(--b);font-weight:600;font-size:13px;color:var(--t2);background:var(--surface);
    border:1px solid var(--border);padding:8px 15px;cursor:pointer;border-radius:20px;transition:.15s}
  .tab.on{color:#fff;background:var(--sunset);border-color:transparent}
  .tab:hover:not(.on){color:var(--text);border-color:var(--border-s)}
  .panel{display:none;animation:f .3s} .panel.on{display:block}
  @keyframes f{from{opacity:0;transform:translateY(5px)}to{opacity:1;transform:none}}
  .grid{display:grid;gap:15px} .g2{grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr}
  .card{background:var(--surface);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:14px;padding:18px 20px;
    box-shadow:0 1px 2px rgba(20,40,60,.05)}
  .card h3{font-family:var(--d);font-weight:600;font-size:17px;margin-bottom:2px;color:var(--head)}
  .card .note{font-size:12.5px;color:var(--t2);margin-bottom:14px}
  .chartbox{position:relative;width:100%}
  .prog{margin-bottom:18px}.prog:last-child{margin-bottom:0}
  .prog .top{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:baseline;margin-bottom:7px}
  .prog .lab{font-size:13px;color:var(--t2)}
  .prog .val{font-family:var(--d);font-weight:600;font-size:17px}
  .prog .val small{color:var(--t3);font-weight:400;font-size:12px}
  .track{height:11px;background:var(--raised);border-radius:6px;overflow:hidden}
  .track i{display:block;height:100%;border-radius:6px;transition:width .7s}
  .track i.p{background:var(--sunset)} .track i.c{background:linear-gradient(90deg,var(--orange),var(--gold))}
  .hint{font-size:11.5px;color:var(--t3);margin-top:6px}
  .stat{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr);gap:10px;margin-bottom:4px}
  .stat .s{background:var(--raised);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:13px;padding:13px 15px}
  .stat .k{font-family:var(--m);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.07em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--t3)}
  .stat .v{font-family:var(--d);font-weight:600;font-size:23px;margin-top:4px}
  .stat .d{font-size:11px;color:var(--t2);margin-top:2px}
  .meals{margin-top:2px}
  .day-h{font-family:var(--m);font-size:10.5px;letter-spacing:.05em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--coral);margin:14px 0 8px}
  .meal{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:12px;padding:11px 0;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border)}
  .meal:last-child{border-bottom:none}
  .meal .nm{flex:1;min-width:0}
  .meal .t{font-weight:600;font-size:13.5px}
  .meal .s{font-size:11.5px;color:var(--t2);margin-top:1px;white-space:nowrap;overflow:hidden;text-overflow:ellipsis}
  .meal .p{font-family:var(--m);font-weight:700;font-size:14px;color:var(--coral);white-space:nowrap}
  .meal .cal{font-family:var(--m);font-size:12px;color:var(--t2);white-space:nowrap;width:62px;text-align:right}
  .recomp{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr);gap:12px;margin-bottom:16px}
  .rc{background:var(--raised);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:14px;padding:16px 18px}
  .rc .k{font-family:var(--m);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.07em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--t3)}
  .rc .v{font-family:var(--d);font-weight:600;font-size:25px;margin-top:5px}
  .rc .d{font-size:11.5px;color:var(--t2);margin-top:3px}
  .insight{background:var(--raised);border:1px solid var(--border);border-left:3px solid var(--coral);
    border-radius:0 12px 12px 0;padding:14px 18px;margin-top:4px;font-size:13px;color:var(--t2)}
  .insight b{color:var(--text);font-weight:600}
  table td{font-size:12.5px}
  .foot{margin-top:26px;padding-top:16px;border-top:1px solid var(--border);font-size:11.5px;color:var(--t3);font-family:var(--m)}
  @media(max-width:720px){.g2{grid-template-columns:1fr}.stat{grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr)}.recomp{grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr}h1{font-size:27px}}
</style>
</head>
<body>
<h2 class="sr-only">Nutrition and recomposition dashboard, light clinical theme.</h2>
<header>
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="hbar"></div>
    <div class="eyebrow">Food log × recomp · weight-neutral</div>
    <h1>Nutrition &amp; recomp</h1>
    <div class="sub">Drop fat, build muscle, hold ~75kg · targets 150g protein / ~2,600 cal</div>
  </div>
</header>
<div class="wrap">
  <nav>
    <button class="tab on" data-p="today">Today</button>
    <button class="tab" data-p="trends">Daily trends</button>
    <button class="tab" data-p="meals">Meals</button>
    <button class="tab" data-p="recomp">Recomp</button>
    <button class="tab" data-p="training">Training</button>
    <button class="tab" data-p="bloods">Bloods</button>
  </nav>
  <section class="panel on" id="today">
    <div class="grid g2">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Saturday — so far</h3>
        <h3>Saturday — final</h3>
        <div class="note">Legs day · oats, shake, chilli-egg brunch, BBQ chicken dinner. Day closed out.</div>
        <div class="prog">
          <div class="top"><span class="lab">Protein</span><span class="val">179<small> / 150 g</small></span></div>
          <div class="track"><i class="p" style="width:100%"></i></div>
          <div class="hint">Cleared by 29 g — strong on a lifting day</div>
        </div>
        <div class="prog">
          <div class="top"><span class="lab">Calories</span><span class="val">2,114<small> / 2,350 burn</small></span></div>
          <div class="track"><i class="c" style="width:90%"></i></div>
          <div class="hint">−236 net — on-target deficit on a low-burn day</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Today's macro split</h3>
        <div class="note">Grams by macro so far.</div>
        <div class="chartbox" style="height:200px"><canvas id="ring"></canvas></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card" style="margin-top:15px">
      <h3>Energy balance — Saturday</h3>
      <div class="note">Garmin burn 2,350 (legs only, no ride) vs everything logged. Day closed out.</div>
      <div class="stat" style="grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr)">
        <div class="s"><div class="k">Burned</div><div class="v">2,350<small style="font-size:12px;color:var(--t3)"> cal</small></div><div class="d">Garmin · legs day</div></div>
        <div class="s"><div class="k">Eaten</div><div class="v">2,114<small style="font-size:12px;color:var(--t3)"> cal</small></div><div class="d">7 items logged</div></div>
        <div class="s"><div class="k">Net</div><div class="v" style="color:#74c490">−236<small style="font-size:12px;color:var(--t3)"> cal</small></div><div class="d">deficit · on target</div></div>
      </div>
      <div style="margin-top:14px">
        <div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;font-size:11px;color:var(--t3);font-family:var(--m);margin-bottom:5px"><span>EATEN 2,114</span><span>BURN 2,350</span></div>
        <div class="track" style="height:14px"><i style="width:90%;background:linear-gradient(90deg,var(--coral),var(--orange))"></i></div>
        <div class="hint">Bar shows eaten as a share of burned — a clean, modest deficit.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="insight" style="margin-top:14px;border-left-color:#74c490"><b>Nicely judged.</b> On a low-burn legs day you landed −236 — a sensible deficit without starving the day before a long ride. Protein 179 g (cleared 150 again), and the dinner kept carbs in for tomorrow. Five-day average is now −302/day (~0.3 kg/week), dead on target. Check readiness in the morning, then fuel the ride properly.</div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="panel" id="trends">
    <div class="card" style="margin-bottom:15px">
      <h3>Daily protein vs 150 g target</h3>
      <div class="note">The number that drives recomp. Dashed line is target; Thursday is still filling up.</div>
      <div class="chartbox" style="height:240px"><canvas id="pchart"></canvas></div>
    </div>
    <div class="grid g2">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Calories vs maintenance</h3>
        <div class="note">Bars = calories eaten. Blue line = actual daily burn (Garmin). Bar sitting below the line = that day's deficit.</div>
        <div class="chartbox" style="height:210px"><canvas id="cchart"></canvas></div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Macro grams by day</h3>
        <div class="note">Protein, fat, carbs side by side.</div>
        <div class="chartbox" style="height:210px"><canvas id="mchart"></canvas></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="panel" id="meals">
    <div class="card">
      <h3>Logged meals</h3>
      <div class="note">Protein and calories per item. Coral figure is protein.</div>
      <div class="meals" id="mealList"></div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="panel" id="recomp">
    <div class="card" style="margin-bottom:15px;border-left:3px solid var(--coral)">
      <h3>Weekly deficit <span style="font-size:12px;color:var(--t3);font-weight:400">· refreshed Sunday eve</span></h3>
      <div class="note">Sum of each day's net (eaten − Garmin burn) across the week — the number that actually moves the scale. Week of Mon 15 – Sun 21 Jun.</div>
      <div class="stat">
        <div class="s"><div class="k">Week total</div><div class="v" style="color:#74c490">−1,510<small style="font-size:12px;color:var(--t3)"> cal</small></div><div class="d">5 days in</div></div>
        <div class="s"><div class="k">Predicted loss</div><div class="v" style="color:#74c490">~0.20<small style="font-size:12px;color:var(--t3)"> kg</small></div><div class="d">deficit ÷ 7700</div></div>
        <div class="s"><div class="k">Days logged</div><div class="v">5<small style="font-size:12px;color:var(--t3)"> / 7</small></div><div class="d">Mon n/a · Sun pending</div></div>
        <div class="s"><div class="k">Avg / day</div><div class="v" style="color:#74c490">−302<small style="font-size:12px;color:var(--t3)"> cal</small></div><div class="d">~0.3 kg/wk pace</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="insight" style="border-left-color:#74c490"><b>Week 1 of tracking — partial.</b> Tue–Sat ran to −1,510 (≈0.20 kg). Monday wasn't logged and Sunday's long ride is still to come — that'll add a solid chunk, likely landing the week near −2,000 (~0.26 kg). I'll finalise this Sunday evening once the ride and the day's food are in. From next week this also shows vs the prior week, so the cut's pace is obvious at a glance.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card" style="margin-bottom:15px">
      <h3>Baseline — 17 Jun</h3>
      <div class="note">The scale holds ~flat by design. Progress shows here: waist down, lifts up.</div>
      <div class="recomp">
        <div class="rc"><div class="k">Weight</div><div class="v">75<small style="font-size:13px;color:var(--t3)"> kg</small></div><div class="d">hold steady</div></div>
        <div class="rc"><div class="k">Waist</div><div class="v">75<small style="font-size:13px;color:var(--t3)"> cm</small></div><div class="d">30" · lean start</div></div>
        <div class="rc"><div class="k">Bench top set</div><div class="v">75<small style="font-size:13px;color:var(--t3)"> kg</small></div><div class="d">building</div></div>
        <div class="rc"><div class="k">Cable row top</div><div class="v">95<small style="font-size:13px;color:var(--t3)"> kg</small></div><div class="d">recent PB</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="insight"><b>How to read recomp:</b> at 75 cm / 30" you're already lean, so change will be gradual — even 1–2 cm off the waist over a couple of months, while the scale holds ~75 kg and bench/row/RDL climb, means it's working. Judge it monthly, not daily.</div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="panel" id="training">
    <div class="card" style="margin-bottom:15px;border-left:3px solid var(--coral)">
      <h3>Today's session — Sat 20 Jun</h3>
      <div class="note">Legs · logged via Hevy · 36 min · green-light day, full session + extra.</div>
      <div class="stat" style="grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr)">
        <div class="s"><div class="k">RDL top set</div><div class="v">75<small style="font-size:12px;color:var(--t3)"> kg</small></div><div class="d">× 10 — PB 🎯</div></div>
        <div class="s"><div class="k">Split squat</div><div class="v">25<small style="font-size:12px;color:var(--t3)"> kg</small></div><div class="d">× 10/side · 3 sets</div></div>
        <div class="s"><div class="k">Leg curl</div><div class="v">57.5<small style="font-size:12px;color:var(--t3)"> kg</small></div><div class="d">× 12 · progressed</div></div>
        <div class="s"><div class="k">Volume</div><div class="v">5<small style="font-size:12px;color:var(--t3)"> lifts</small></div><div class="d">extra sets added</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="insight" style="margin-top:14px">Did <b>more</b> than the plan, not less — RDL ramped to 75 kg × 10, well past the 60 kg target and a working PB, plus extra sets on extensions and curls. The 36 min is just tight 30–60s rest, not a cut session. Heavy leg load the day before a long ride, so fuel carbs into tonight; legs may feel it early tomorrow but Z2 will spin it out.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card" style="margin-bottom:15px;border-left:3px solid var(--coral)">
      <h3>Yesterday — Fri 19 Jun</h3>
      <div class="note">Easy Z2 · Albert Park laps · the amber-day call, kept honest.</div>
      <div class="stat" style="grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr)">
        <div class="s"><div class="k">Distance</div><div class="v">31<small style="font-size:12px;color:var(--t3)"> km</small></div><div class="d">64 min moving</div></div>
        <div class="s"><div class="k">Avg power</div><div class="v">141<small style="font-size:12px;color:var(--t3)"> W</small></div><div class="d">~58% FTP · true Z2</div></div>
        <div class="s"><div class="k">Avg HR</div><div class="v">138<small style="font-size:12px;color:var(--t3)"> bpm</small></div><div class="d">aerobic · max 160</div></div>
        <div class="s"><div class="k">Cadence</div><div class="v">90<small style="font-size:12px;color:var(--t3)"> rpm</small></div><div class="d">630 cal active</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="insight" style="margin-top:14px">Exactly right for an amber morning — 141 W is ~58% of FTP and HR stayed aerobic, so this is genuinely restorative, not a Z3 drift. Good discipline. Watered &amp; refuelled after with a 60 g-protein smoothie. Tomorrow's readout decides the long ride.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card" style="margin-bottom:15px;border-left:3px solid var(--coral)">
      <h3>Thu 18 Jun · AM</h3>
      <div class="note">Sweet Spot 4×8 · FTP-block opener · on the trainer.</div>
      <div class="stat" style="grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr)">
        <div class="s"><div class="k">Target</div><div class="v">235<small style="font-size:12px;color:var(--t3)">–245 W</small></div><div class="d">sweet spot</div></div>
        <div class="s"><div class="k">Completed</div><div class="v">3.25<small style="font-size:12px;color:var(--t3)"> / 4</small></div><div class="d">3 full + 2 min</div></div>
        <div class="s"><div class="k">Time at SS</div><div class="v">~26<small style="font-size:12px;color:var(--t3)"> min</small></div><div class="d">of 32 target</div></div>
        <div class="s"><div class="k">Fuel</div><div class="v">50<small style="font-size:12px;color:var(--t3)"> g</small></div><div class="d">carbs intra-ride</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="insight" style="margin-top:14px">Brutal final interval — faded to 2 of 8 min. Normal for an opener; the work banked still drives the adaptation. Next time, pace the first three a touch easier or fuel slightly earlier to chase the full set.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card" style="margin-bottom:15px;border-left:3px solid var(--coral)">
      <h3>Thu 18 Jun · PM — Chest &amp; shoulders</h3>
      <div class="note">Weights session · logged via Hevy · ~46 min · the recommended PM block.</div>
      <div class="stat" style="grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr)">
        <div class="s"><div class="k">Bench top set</div><div class="v">77.5<small style="font-size:12px;color:var(--t3)"> kg</small></div><div class="d">× 6 — new PB 🎯</div></div>
        <div class="s"><div class="k">Incline DB</div><div class="v">50<small style="font-size:12px;color:var(--t3)"> kg</small></div><div class="d">× 10 · total</div></div>
        <div class="s"><div class="k">OH press DB</div><div class="v">25<small style="font-size:12px;color:var(--t3)"> kg</small></div><div class="d">× 10 · total</div></div>
        <div class="s"><div class="k">Volume</div><div class="v">5<small style="font-size:12px;color:var(--t3)"> lifts</small></div><div class="d">+ lat raise, wrist</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="insight" style="margin-top:14px">Bench 77.5 kg × 6 clears your 75 kg mark — strength is trending up. Back-off sets at 67.5 × 10 banked quality volume. Paired with this morning's Sweet Spot that's a real double day, so protein and sleep tonight are the priority for recovery.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card" style="margin-bottom:15px">
      <h3>Where your fitness sits</h3>
      <div class="note">Headline markers from Strava + the gym.</div>
      <div class="stat">
        <div class="s"><div class="k">FTP</div><div class="v">243<small style="font-size:12px;color:var(--t3)"> W</small></div><div class="d">3.24 W/kg · 6-wk est · 257 '26 high · 275 goal</div></div>
        <div class="s"><div class="k">VO₂ max</div><div class="v">49.6</div><div class="d">peak 51.6 · strong</div></div>
        <div class="s"><div class="k">Cable row</div><div class="v">95<small style="font-size:12px;color:var(--t3)"> kg</small></div><div class="d">recent PB</div></div>
        <div class="s"><div class="k">Bench</div><div class="v">77.5<small style="font-size:12px;color:var(--t3)"> kg</small></div><div class="d">× 6 · new PB</div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card" style="margin-bottom:15px">
      <h3>Energy balance — day-matched</h3>
      <div class="note">Eaten vs Garmin actual burn, same day, for the 5 logged days (16–20 Jun). Your 4-week typical burn is 2,741/day for reference.</div>
      <div class="stat">
        <div class="s"><div class="k">Avg eaten</div><div class="v">2,347<small style="font-size:12px;color:var(--t3)"> cal</small></div><div class="d">5 days</div></div>
        <div class="s"><div class="k">Avg burned</div><div class="v">2,649<small style="font-size:12px;color:var(--t3)"> cal</small></div><div class="d">Garmin actual</div></div>
        <div class="s"><div class="k">Avg net</div><div class="v" style="color:#74c490">−302<small style="font-size:12px;color:var(--t3)"> cal</small></div><div class="d">day-matched</div></div>
        <div class="s"><div class="k">Per week</div><div class="v" style="color:#74c490">~0.3<small style="font-size:12px;color:var(--t3)"> kg</small></div><div class="d">on target</div></div>
      </div>
      <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(5,1fr);gap:8px;margin-top:14px">
        <div style="background:var(--raised);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:11px;padding:10px 10px">
          <div style="font-family:var(--m);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.03em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--coral)">Tue</div>
          <div style="font-size:10.5px;color:var(--t2);margin-top:5px">2155·2450</div>
          <div style="font-family:var(--d);font-weight:600;font-size:16px;color:var(--sky);margin-top:2px">−295</div>
        </div>
        <div style="background:var(--raised);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:11px;padding:10px 10px">
          <div style="font-family:var(--m);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.03em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--coral)">Wed</div>
          <div style="font-size:10.5px;color:var(--t2);margin-top:5px">2520·2614</div>
          <div style="font-family:var(--d);font-weight:600;font-size:16px;color:var(--sky);margin-top:2px">−94</div>
        </div>
        <div style="background:var(--raised);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:11px;padding:10px 10px">
